The paper deals with the topic of differential privacy, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of algorithms and data structures for computing queries on databases, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the concept of privacy and utility. The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it deals with the concept of risk-averse consumers. Finally, the paper involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with the concept of Bayesian consumers.
